          </strong>
          Recorded emergency information, (800) 705-9998
         </li>
         <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>
           Radio:
          </strong>
          KALX (90.7 FM)
         </li>
         <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>
           For help, dial 642-3333
          </strong>
          (UCPD)
          <strong>
           or 911
          </strong>
          (on or off campus)
         </li>
        </ul>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6">
       <h2>
        Status
       </h2>
       <p>
        There are no emergencies or emergency communications in effect for the UC Berkeley
    campus. If an emergency occurs, the latest information will be posted on
        <a href="http://news.berkeley.edu">
         Berkeley News
        </a>
        . This page is a backup emergency website, hosted offsite, that will be updated only if service to the main UC Berkeley information websites (
        <a href="http://berkeley.edu">
         berkeley.edu
        </a>
        and
        <a href="http://news.berkeley.edu">
         news.berkeley.edu
        </a>
        ) is disrupted.
       </p>
       <p>
        The campus emergency sirens are tested at noon on the first Wednesday of each month. At all other times, when you hear the sirens you should::
       </p>
       <ul>
        <li>
         Shelter in place
        </li>
        <li>
         Shut doors and windows
        </li>
        <li>
         Seek instructions and information (see right)
        </li>
       </ul>
       <p>
        Information about preparing for a campus emergency is available from the
        <a href="http://oem.berkeley.edu">
         Office
of Emergency Management
        </a>
        website. The current
        <a href="http://systemstatus.berkeley.edu/">
         status of campus computer systems
        </a>
        also is available online.
       </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-3">
       <div class="block list-block">
        <ul class="list-group">
         <li class="list-group-item">
